    "body": "### Problem\n\nIn vim and neovim, `<C-[>` is supposed to always be equivalent to ESC, regardless of mappings. However, after an update of neovim, I can no longer use `<C-[>` to exit terminal mode, while ESC still works.\n\nI just recently updated from a nightly nvim 0.11 from the june 14, 2024 nightly:\n```\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-242+gba70404c5\nBuild type: RelWithDebInfo\nLuaJIT 2.1.1716656478\nRun \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n```\n\nto the latest stable release of 0.11.1:\n```\nNVIM v0.11.1\nBuild type: Release\nLuaJIT 2.1.1741730670\nRun \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n```\n\nI have mapped ESC to exit normal mode in my [vim-termhere](https://github.com/TamaMcGlinn/vim-termhere) plugin, but the following line is all you need, I can reproduce the bug with `nvim -u NONE` and setting this mapping:\n```\ntnoremap <ESC> <C-\\><C-n>\n```\n\nI still have both versions, so I can easily test other things if you ask me in this thread.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nnvim --clean\n:tnoremap <ESC> <C-\\><C-n>\n:term\na\n<C-[>\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`<C-[>` should exit terminal mode back into normal mode. Note that ESC does still work.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.11.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, vim 8.2 does not seem to even allow exiting terminal mode using ESC\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 22.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nboth Gnome Version 3.44.0 for GNOME 42 and Kitty 0.35.2, same behaviour\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nnightly from last year was an appimage, new install is via deb pkg from neovim-releases repo",
